---
description: graphify knowledge graph context
alwaysApply: true
---

This monorepo’s knowledge graph is built from the **repository root** (`graphify-out/`). It covers first‑party code and docs across **backend** (`src/`, `api/`, `scripts/`), **portals** (`Frontend/`, `MainAdmin/`, `admin/`, `new portal/`), **Supabase** (`supabase/`), **SQL/RPC** (`rpc_functions/`, `migration_script/`), **shared docs** (`docs/`, `implementation-docs/`, `examples/`), and the rest of the tree—subject to `.graphifyignore` (dependencies, `.next/`/`dist/`/`build/`, secrets, `graphify-out/`).

- Before answering architecture or codebase questions, read `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` for god nodes and community structure.
- If `graphify-out/wiki/index.md` exists, navigate it instead of reading raw files when it helps.
- After meaningful code or SQL changes in this session, run **`graphify update .`** from the repo root to refresh the graph (AST-only for code/SQL, no API cost). For a full semantic rebuild from the IDE, use **`/graphify .`** at the root when appropriate.
- If `graphify-out/graph.html` is missing, the graph likely exceeded the default HTML size limit; use **`graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md`**, **`graphify-out/graph.json`**, and **`graphify query "…"`** (or raise **`GRAPHIFY_VIZ_NODE_LIMIT`** before rebuild) instead of the HTML viewer.
